#. [campaign]: id=The_South_Guard
#. Adding “Start Here” is meant to attract players looking for a tutorial,
#. without dissuading players who'd skip something that’s purely a tutorial.
#. Translations can’t be much longer than the English string, otherwise the
#. left column of the campaign dialog becomes noticeably wide.
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/_main.cfg:34
msgid "The South Guard — Start Here"
msgstr "南部防衛隊 — 初心者向け"

#. [campaign]: id=The_South_Guard
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/_main.cfg:35
msgid "TSG"
msgstr "TSG"

#. [campaign]: id=The_South_Guard
#: data/campaigns/The_South_Guard/_main.cfg:44
msgid ""
"A young knight, Deoran, is dispatched to the southern frontier town of Westin. Thrust quickly into a hapless conflict against marauding bandits, Deoran soon encounters darker forces at play. Rally the South Guard and defend your homes!\n"
"\n"
"<i><b>This is the recommended starting campaign.</b></i>\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"若き騎士 Deoran は南部辺境の町 Westin に派遣された。無法者との戦闘に巻き込まれた Deoran は、やがて背後で暗躍する邪悪な力の存在に気付く。南部防衛隊を再編し、国土を守るのだ！\n"
"\n"
"<i><b>最初のキャンペーンとしてはこれがオススメです。</b></i>\n"

